{
  "stem": "8370.4",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I have nothing again, but I must have a permission from my authorities.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "They say, don't worry.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "We will arrange this.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, they have done this very quick, maybe-- I don't know.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "In maybe one week time, I receive an order sent from Frankfurt-- because there was a general-- was a headquarter of General Eisenhower, and afterwards of General Clay, who was commanding general of the American occupation zone in Germany-- that I am, I have to join the prosecution and judge division of the US Army for war criminals and report to a village, Dachau, which was south of Munich, between Munich and Garmisch-Partenkirchen, beautiful ski resort there, to the commanding officer, I remember Colonel Fainter, to start my duty there.",
      "word_count": 90
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And Dachau was a former big, really, first German concentration camp far before the war, the oldest one.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But when I arrived there, it was the springtime '46.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "There was full of 41,000 SS and war criminals.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "There was a special camp, for example, where you have the generals and ministers and the top Gestapo people with Marshal Milch of the air force, with Kesselring who was marshal in charge of the army in Italy, who was plenty of-- I remember a personal doctor of Hitler, and so on, Gestapo people, Gestapo Muller, the famous one-- infamous one, and so on and so on.",
      "word_count": 67
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And for the beginning, I was put in charge of security of this general camp.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "There was an administrative officer.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "It was an American sergeant.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "It was a doctor, American captain, a doctor, chief doctor.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "Because it was together with a hospital camp combined.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And I was, I say, in charge of security.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "So I had guards all around.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "You know, I have to check their post, reading incoming letters and outgoing letters.",
      "word_count": 14
    }
  ],
